cli_comprehensive_analysis.metadata: Comprehensive analysis of MGQ.AX (Macquarie Goodman Group) which was an active ASX-listed real estate company from February 2005 to July 2007. The ticker was changed to GMG.AX (Goodman Group) following corporate restructuring when Macquarie Bank exited its involvement.

company_overview.historical_status: MGQ.AX was the ticker for Macquarie Goodman Group, listed on ASX from February 2005 until July 5, 2007
company_overview.business_focus: Industrial property group specializing in logistics and warehousing real estate
company_overview.corporate_transformation: Company restructured in 2007, with Macquarie Bank selling its 7.7% stake and the entity becoming Goodman Group (GMG.AX)
company_overview.current_successor: Goodman Group (GMG.AX) - one of the largest property groups on ASX with A$73.4B market cap as of August 2025
